  "text": "The main result from Ref. [CITATION_1] was that in the absence of ISR and MPI, the peak in the √ s min distribution nicely correlates with the mass threshold of the newly produced particles. This observation provides one generic relation between the total mass of the produced particles and the total mass M of the invisible particles. Based on several SUSY examples involving fully hadronic signatures in symmetric as well as asymmetric topologies, Ref. [CITATION_2] showed that the accuracy of this measurement rivals the one achieved with the more traditional M T 2 methods.",
